comments.body: @sandbergja I have ruby, bundler, and yarn installed on my computer. However, as I was installing lando, when I clicked on the executable file, the Windows protection alert popped up stating it blocked the installer from running. I am not familiar with lando, but when I looked it up apparently the warning for Windows users has been popping up regarding lando for several years. Nobody seemed to have a good solution regarding how to handle it or stated if it was safe to proceed with the download. Is there a way I can work on this project without using lando? If not, I am sorry but I can't continue working on the project because I am concerned about downloading the program with that warning.

@Phil94comp -- good to know about that Windows warning, thanks for the info!  An alternative would be to not run `rake dss:servers:start`, and instead:

- Install Apache solr locally
- Edit config/blacklight.yml locally to point to your local version of solr
- Install Postgresql server locally
- Edit config/db.yml locally to point to your local version of postgresql
